-------------------------------------------------------------------------
Third-party software
-------------------------------------------------------------------------

This software depends on third-party libraries that are distributed under
their own license terms. A full enumeration of every direct and
transitive dependency — across compile, runtime, provided and test
scopes — is generated by the build into THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.txt at the
root of the repository. Regenerate with:

    mvn license:add-third-party

License families observed in the current dependency tree:

  - Apache License 2.0          (the bulk of AWS SDK, Micronaut, Jackson,
                                 Netty, Apache Commons, Joda-Time, …)
  - MIT / MIT-0                 (SLF4J, reactive-streams, YahooFinanceAPI)
  - EPL 2.0 / EDL 1.0 /
    GPL2 with Classpath Exception (Jakarta Mail, Jakarta Annotations)
  - EPL 1.0 / LGPL              (Logback Classic / Core)
  - LGPL                        (JFreeChart)
  - Apache 2.0 OR LGPL 2.1+     (JNA)

JFreeChart is the only LGPL-only direct dependency. It is linked
dynamically as a Maven artifact, so downstream consumers retain their
LGPL right to replace it without having to re-license this project.

See THIRD_PARTY_LICENSES.txt for the exhaustive list and project URLs.
